CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 3, 1958, pg. 14 reads: "Service Award - William S. Howell, right, director of Kay Boys Club, smiles as he receives a plaque, presented by his pastor, the Rev. A. C. Sumpter, on behalf of St. James AME Church in recognition of his meritorious service in the church and community. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Rev. A. C. Sumpter of St. James AME Church, presenting service plaque to William S. Howell, director of Kay Boys Club, posed in interior with light colored walls, and stairs with patterned rug
